# Terminal and HTTP commands

This project runs on Windows PowerShell. Agents often hang integrated terminals with silent, untimed `curl` calls. Follow these rules.

## curl on Windows

- Always use `curl.exe`, never bare `curl` (PowerShell aliases it to `Invoke-WebRequest`).
- Always pass `--max-time`: `2` for localhost, `15` for external URLs.
- Do not use `-s` when debugging; prefer visible output or `-f` with a timeout.
- Local health check:

```powershell
curl.exe -sf --max-time 2 http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/config
```

- Before probing localhost, confirm the server is running (or use `start.bat`, which waits up to 30s).

## Prefer project scripts

- Start app: `start.bat`
- Tests: `npm test`

Do not invent one-off network fetches when a script or committed file already exists.
